clinical_particulars.therapeutic_indications: Indicated for the treatment of chronic hepatitis B in adult patients with evidence of active viral replication and either evidence of persistent elevations in serum aminotransferases ALT or AST or histologically active disease this is based on histological virological biochemical and serological responses in adult patients with HBeAg and HBeAg chronic hepatitis B with compensated liver function and in adult patients with clinical evidence of lamivudine resistant hepatitis B virus with either compensated or decompensated liver function

contraindications.disease: Renal tubular nephropathy characterized by histological alterations and or increases in BUN and serum creatinine was the primary dose limiting toxicity associated with administration of adefovir dipivoxil in animals Nephrotoxicity was observed in animals at systemic exposures approximately 3 ndash 10 times higher than those in humans at the recommended therapeutic dose of 10 mg day
contraindications.pharmacodynamics: Adefovir dipivoxil a diester prodrug of adefovir Adefovir is an acyclic nucleotide analog with activity against human hepatitis B virus HBV The concentration of adefovir that inhibited 50 of viral DNA synthesis IC50 in vitro ranged from 0 2 to 2 5 mu M in HBV transfected human hepatoma cell lines The combination of adefovir with lamivudine showed additive anti HBV activity
